move on, and play a new game.</i>

116
00:07:19,714 --> 00:07:22,466
I said <i>no, I'm
gonna keep playing.</i>

117
00:07:24,352 --> 00:07:27,935
<i>I'm going to play a few moves and then
maybe get a check or two;</i>

118
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:29,502
<i>and THEN I'll resign.</i>

119
00:07:34,230 --> 00:07:37,625
So what do I do? I play c5.

120
00:07:37,650 --> 00:07:40,861
If I'm going to get a check with my
pieces that are all the way back here,

121
00:07:40,886 --> 00:07:42,741
then I need to get these
pawns out of the way.

122
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:50,705
So I sacrifice a pawn. He
takes; I take back -

123
00:07:50,730 --> 00:07:54,665
I DON'T take back.
I bring in the Knight.

124
00:07:54,690 --> 00:07:58,121
<i>If you want this pawn, sir,
go ahead and take it:</i>

125
00:07:58,146 --> 00:08:03,365
<i>and that'll give me the open
file against your King.</i>

126
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:06,602
He correctly ignores my
suggestion to take with the pawn,

127
00:08:06,626 --> 00:08:09,254
and he takes with
the Rook instead.

128
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:13,835
I go here. I get the half-open
file, and I'm like <i>all right:</i>

129
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:16,021
<i>somehow I'm going to get this c-pawn
out of the way.</i>

130
00:08:16,046 --> 00:08:18,785
<i>I don't know HOW I'm going to do it, yet.</i>

131
00:08:18,810 --> 00:08:22,385
<i>But I'm going to do it. That's what I'm
going to do. I'm going to get your King.</i>

132
00:08:22,410 --> 00:08:25,925
<i>Somehow, sir.</i>

133
00:08:25,950 --> 00:08:29,195
He develops his Knight;

134
00:08:29,220 --> 00:08:32,915
reinforces this pawn;
and he's doing good, here.

135
00:08:32,940 --> 00:08:36,755
a3. What's the idea of
a3? I want to push b4!

136
00:08:36,780 --> 00:08:39,390
If I push b4 right away, he
just takes with the a-pawn.

137
00:08:40,590 --> 00:08:45,875
... g5. What? He is quite properly
ignoring my attack on the Queenside,

138
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,645
which is doomed to failure,

139
00:08:47,670 --> 00:08:49,850
and he says <i>what am I gonna
do? I need to develop my Queen,</i>

140
00:08:49,875 --> 00:08:53,765
<i>and my Rook, so I'm gonna
push these pawns in front of them:</i>

141
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:56,780
<i>and then not only am I developing
my Queen, and my Rook,</i>

142
00:08:56,805 --> 00:08:59,045
<i>I'm also attacking your King.</i>

143
00:08:59,070 --> 00:09:03,156
When you're up a Queen, what do
you do you? You try to end the game.

144
00:09:03,181 --> 00:09:06,155
Okay. I push b4.

145
00:09:06,180 --> 00:09:08,135
He takes. I take.

146
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:11,238
He pushes ... g4.

147
00:09:11,263 --> 00:09:15,473
Kingside attack! <i>You're not the
only one that can attack, Matt.</i>

148
00:09:15,498 --> 00:09:18,602
Now my Bishop's under attack, and I have to
be very careful what I do here,

149
00:09:18,627 --> 00:09:21,826
because when I'm -
when you're down,

150
00:09:21,851 --> 00:09:23,493
you need to keep your
pieces on the board.

151
00:09:23,518 --> 00:09:26,526
If you let your pieces
be traded off the board,

152
00:09:26,550 --> 00:09:32,902
then any hope you may
have evaporates in smoke.

153
00:09:34,161 --> 00:09:38,255
That is to say the <i>trade
offer</i> is a powerful weapon,

154
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:41,885
in the hands of the person
who is ahead in material.

155
00:09:41,910 --> 00:09:44,945
So, I retreat,

156
00:09:44,970 --> 00:09:47,438
and he brings out
his Knight further.

157
00:09:47,463 --> 00:09:49,875
He's going to go here; he's
going to attack my Bishop;

158
00:09:49,899 --> 00:09:55,870
he's going to soften up the g-pawn;
he's going to just take the pawn.

159
00:09:55,895 --> 00:09:58,140
He's got all kinds of
good stuff going on here.

160
00:09:58,165 --> 00:10:01,159
I don't want my pawn to
be taken, so I'm like <i>all right,</i>

161
00:10:01,184 --> 00:10:04,096
<i>this pawn's going to die
but he's going to give his all.</i>

162
00:10:04,121 --> 00:10:07,207
<i>He's going to
take out this pawn,</i>

163
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:12,787
<i>which is supporting this pawn, which is
covering the King, so I'm going to take it.</i>

164
