This is perfectly fine.

166
00:10:18,302 --> 00:10:19,867
Perfectly fine move.

167
00:10:19,892 --> 00:10:24,320
It does mean though, that are no pawns
covering his King anymore.

168
00:10:24,345 --> 00:10:30,187
He might have to deal with the
fact that, after I move my Knight,

169
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:35,355
his Knight is completely pinned against
the King, and it cannot move at all.

170
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:38,621
So that's what I do. I'm
like <i>all right, I'm gonna go</i>

171
00:10:38,645 --> 00:10:41,197
<i>pile up on this pawn
that you pushed,</i>

172
00:10:41,222 --> 00:10:44,647
<i>and I'm gonna realize this pin
I'm pinning against your King.</i>

173
00:10:44,672 --> 00:10:47,497
He says, <i>all right, I'm
going to protect my pawn;</i>

174
00:10:47,522 --> 00:10:49,747
<i>and by the way I'm going
to attack your Knight;</i>

175
00:10:49,772 --> 00:10:54,187
<i>and I'm going to get my Queen developed;
and maybe I'll slide a Rook behind it;</i>

176
00:10:54,212 --> 00:10:57,727
<i>and I'm coming for you, Matt.</i>

177
00:10:57,752 --> 00:11:02,888
So, I play this Bishop move, because
I don't want my Knight to be destroyed.

178
00:11:02,912 --> 00:11:04,557
Remember what I said:
<i>if you're down material</i>

179
00:11:04,581 --> 00:11:07,778
<i>you want to keep what
pieces you have on the board,</i>

180
00:11:07,802 --> 00:11:10,345
<i>and hope, and
pray, for a miracle.</i>

181
00:11:11,552 --> 00:11:15,158
He brings his Knight over here.

182
00:11:15,183 --> 00:11:20,227
The Bishop isn't there anymore, but
the pawn is. So he's threatening my King,

183
00:11:20,252 --> 00:11:24,907
and i'm really worried
about this Knight fork.

184
00:11:24,932 --> 00:11:27,427
You can't play the
Knight fork right away.

185
00:11:27,452 --> 00:11:29,797
It LOOKS like you
can, because I've got

186
00:11:29,822 --> 00:11:32,377
one,

187
00:11:32,402 --> 00:11:35,167
two attackers on that square;

188
00:11:35,192 --> 00:11:38,497
and he's got

189
00:11:38,522 --> 00:11:40,799
the Rook defending it, and
the other Knight defending it;

190
00:11:40,823 --> 00:11:44,977
but remember this Knight is not
REALLY defending, because of this pin.

191
00:11:45,002 --> 00:11:50,306
So if he were to move the Knight fork
work right away, then I would just take.

192
00:11:52,232 --> 00:11:55,267
It would be a free Knight.

193
00:11:55,292 --> 00:12:00,415
But still, it's a concern. So I
move - I move my Rook here.

194
00:12:00,902 --> 00:12:04,321
This stops the Knight fork for good
and all, because you're only attacking

195
00:12:04,346 --> 00:12:06,907
one Rook; and I can
just move the Rook.

196
00:12:06,932 --> 00:12:11,707
And also it brings in the idea of maybe -
maybe I double up the Rooks on the

197
00:12:11,732 --> 00:12:15,170
c-file; or maybe I bring the Rook
over here, and add another attacker

198
00:12:15,195 --> 00:12:17,557
to the b-pawn - to the g-pawn:

199
00:12:17,582 --> 00:12:19,957
I'm activating my Rooks.

